CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 18, 1958, pg. 1 reads: "Unsafe? Unfit? - To keep the city from demolishing these Winfield tenement houses, which allegedly are unsafe and unfit for human habitation, Alfred E. Davis of 7707 Baxter St., the owner, has appealed to Common Pleas Court on the grounds that the city has not allowed him time enough to make the necessary repairs, although, he said, he has repair materials, like the building blocks (arrow) on or near the premises. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Exterior of Winfield tenement houses with clapboard siding, wooden stairs, and pile of concrete blocks, Winfield Street, East Liberty
